706314f-a.title: Brooklyn: Powers Street - Leonard Street
706314f-a.text:
(1)
108 Powers Street, south side, between Leonard Street and Man-
hattan Ave., showing a mosque housing the Democratic Club of the
13 A.D. in 1929, in 1937 it belonged to the American Mohammedan
Society. A story, pertinent to this, the only mosque in New York
City, was carried in the Herald Tribune of September 5, 1937.
October 12, 1937.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
(2)
The same, more extensive.
October 12, 1937.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
An article on this structure appeared in the Herald Tribune of
September 5, 1937.
